subSubSection.paragraph:
FWs shorter than in males (
Figs 1
; 
3B
; 
7A, B
), slightly overlapping, dark brown with orange veins; venation with five main longitudinal veins and strong transverse ones barely distinguishable the ones from the others, forming a dense network of veins. Lateral field with area between M and R dark as in males.

First instars dark brown with whitish spot on head (
Fig. 7C
); later instars more similar to adults in coloration.
